.TH "ata_host_alloc_pinfo" 9 "ata_host_alloc_pinfo" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_host_alloc_pinfo \- alloc host and init with port_info array
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ata_host *" ata_host_alloc_pinfo
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct ata_port_info * const * ppi "  ","
.BI "int n_ports "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
generic device this host is associated with
.IP "ppi" 12
array of ATA port_info to initialize host with
.IP "n_ports" 12
number of ATA ports attached to this host

Allocate ATA host and initialize with info from \fIppi\fP.  If NULL
terminated, \fIppi\fP may contain fewer entries than \fIn_ports\fP.  The
last entry will be used for the remaining ports.
.SH "RETURN"
Allocate ATA host on success, NULL on failure.

LOCKING:
Inherited from calling layer (may sleep).
